  "text": "Findings summary:\n\n1. SERVO STYLE AND SELECTORS CRATES (servo--be6a2f99):\nIn the current servo repo, there are no 'components/style/' or 'components/selectors/' directories. The style system has been extracted to the external 'servo/stylo' git repository. The workspace Cargo.toml (Cargo.toml) declares both crates as git dependencies:\n  - selectors = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" }\n  - stylo = { git = \"https://github.com/servo/stylo\", rev = \"3b46f3ef27eb14ca276b4bf3ff041a6c43d93827\" } (the renamed 'style' crate)\nThe selectors crate (v0.35.0) depends on: bitflags, cssparser, derive_more, log, new_debug_unreachable, phf, phf_codegen, precomputed-hash, rustc-hash, servo_arc, smallvec, to_shmem, to_shmem_derive.\nThe stylo crate depends on: app_units, arrayvec, atomic_refcell, bitflags, byteorder, cssparser, derive_more, encoding_rs, euclid, icu_segmenter, indexmap, itertools, log, mime, parking_lot, rayon, rustc-hash, selectors, and many more.\n\n2. STYLE SYSTEM ENTRY POINT (servo--be6a2f99):\nThe closest entry point in the servo repo is 'tests/unit/style/lib.rs', which is the test suite for the style system. It declares 'extern crate style' (old name for stylo) and 'extern crate selectors', and includes modules: animated_properties, attr, custom_properties, logical_geometry, parsing, properties, rule_tree, str, stylesheets, stylist. Its Cargo.toml is at 'tests/unit/style/Cargo.toml'.\n\n3. RUST-LANG/RUST DEPENDENCY ON SERVO'S SELECTORS (rust--01f6ddf7):\nThe file 'src/tools/cargotest/main.rs' in rust-lang/rust contains a TEST_REPOS constant that includes a servo entry explicitly testing the 'selectors' package from https://github.com/servo/servo (sha: 785a344e32db58d4e631fd3cae17fd1f29a721ab). The comment reads: 'Only test Stylo a.k.a. Quantum CSS, the parts of Servo going into Firefox.' No crate under compiler/ or library/ directly depends on selectors in its Cargo.toml, but the cargotest tool validates that the Rust compiler can build and test Servo's selectors crate.\n\n4. PROC_MACRO BRIDGE (rust--01f6ddf7):\nThe file 'library/proc_macro/src/bridge/mod.rs' defines the proc_macro bridge — the internal interface for communicating between a proc_macro client (a proc macro crate) and a proc_macro server (the compiler front-end). Key symbols: the 'with_api!' macro (defines the full server RPC API for TokenStream, Span, Symbol, FreeFunctions, Literal operations) and 'BridgeConfig' struct (configuration for establishing an active connection between server and client). The compiler-side wrapper is 'compiler/rustc_proc_macro/Cargo.toml', which points its lib path to '../../library/proc_macro/src/lib.rs'. The server-side implementation is in 'compiler/rustc_expand/src/proc_macro_server.rs', which imports from 'rustc_proc_macro::bridge'."
